issues.recommendation:
Extract the static style object to a module-level constant outside the component so it is created once:

const DOT_TEXTURE_STYLE = {
  backgroundImage: 'radial-gradient(circle, currentColor 1px, transparent 1px)',
  backgroundSize: '20px 20px',
} as const;

Then use `style={DOT_TEXTURE_STYLE}` in JSX.

Add an `accentVar` prop to ProductCardImageProps and pass `categoryTheme.accent` from the parent ProductCard:

// In ProductCard.tsx (parent)
<ProductCardImage
  ...
  accentVar={categoryTheme.accent}
/>

// In ProductCardImage.tsx — remove the getCategoryTheme import and call

Use Next.js dynamic import with ssr:false (Canvas cannot SSR):

import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const FeaturedRibbon = dynamic(
  () => import('./FeaturedRibbon').then(m => ({ default: m.FeaturedRibbon })),
  { ssr: false }
);

This also removes the need to guard `globalThis.window` for devicePixelRatio at module load time.
